cler  Giraldus Cambrensis  (‘Gerald the Welshman’). In the <i>Mabinogi</i>, Angharad Golden Hand at first rejects Peredur's suit, but later falls in love with him when he comes back as the unknown Mute Knight. The name has been strongly revived in Wales since the 1940s, borne, for example, by the actress  Angharad Rees  (  1949-2012 )."],"variants":[]},{"name":"ferch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["1  ‘Sharp blade’.","2  ‘Wind’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Angharad ferch Hywel was born about 1422, in Llangadwaladr, Anglesey, Wales, her father, Hywel ap Ieuan, was 24 and her mother, Mrs. Hywel ap Ieuan, was 20. She had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Heilyn ap Einion Sais."},"et":{"about 1422–":"umbes 1422–Surnud","1422–Female":"1422–Surnud","–1465":"–1465","1440–1538":"1440–1538","1445–Male":"1445–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1400–Male":"1400–Surnud","1404–Female":"1404–Surnud","1404":"1404","1445":"1445","1400":"1400","1422":"1422","1465":"1465","about 1422":"umbes 1422","1440":"1440","about 1445":"umbes 1445","about 1440":"umbes 1440","1538":"1538","Bodorgan, Anglesey, Wales":"Bodorgan, Anglesey, Wales","Bodorgan, Llanferian, Anglesey, Wales":"Bodorgan, Anglesey, Wales, United Kingdom","Llangadwaladr, Anglesey, Wales":"Llangadwaladr, Anglesey, Wales","{Cadrod Hardd}":"Chadrūd, Herāt, Afganistan"},"fi":{"about 1422–":"noin 1422–Kuollut","1422–Female":"1422–Kuollut","–1465":"–1465","1440–1538":"1440–1538","1445–Male":"1445–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1400–Male":"1400–Kuollut","1404–Female":"1404–Kuollut","1404":"1404","1445":"1445","1400":"1400","1422":"1422","1465":"1465","about 1422":"noin 1422","1440":"1440","about 1445":"noin 1445","about 